ðŸ”¹ 3. SIEM Workflow (How it works)

Logs generated from endpoints, firewalls, servers.

Logs forwarded to SIEM (via agents or syslog).

SIEM parses & normalizes logs.

Rules & Correlation detect suspicious activity.

Alerts â†’ SOC Analyst investigates.

ðŸ“Œ Example:

10 failed logins (Event ID 4625) from same IP in 5 minutes â†’ Alert for Brute Force.

ðŸ”¹ 4. Splunk Basics

Query Language = SPL (Search Processing Language)

Example Queries:

index=security sourcetype=windows:security EventCode=4625


â†’ Show all failed logins

index=firewall action=blocked | stats count by src_ip


â†’ Show top blocked IPs

